      <h1 class='title'>Residential Care (Children)</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 27 October 2003 vol 412 c84WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_84ws' title='Col. 84WS &mdash; HC Deb 27 October 2003 vol 412 c84WS' name='column_84ws' href='#column_84ws' rel='bookmark'>84WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0412P0-05071'>
        <a name='S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_423'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-david-davis' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_423' title='Link to this speech by Mr David Davis' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-david-davis" title="Mr David Davis">David Davis</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0412P0-05071">To ask the Secretary of State for Education and Skills how many children were in residential care in<span class="italic">(a)</span> England and (b) the East Riding of Yorkshire in each of the last two years. [134051]</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0412P0-05072'>
        <a name='S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_424'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mrs-margaret-hodge' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_424' title='Link to this speech by Mrs Margaret Hodge' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mrs-margaret-hodge" title="Mrs Margaret Hodge">Margaret Hodge</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0412P0-05072">The latest information available on looked after children in residential care in<span class="italic">(a)</span> England and <span class="italic">(b)</span> the East Riding of Yorkshire is shown in the table.</p><p id="S6CV0412P0-05073">
          <table>
          <tr>
          <td><span class="italic">Number of children in residential care<sup>1</sup> in England and the East Riding of Yorkshire at 31 March 2001 and 2002<sup>2</sup></span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
          <td></td>
          <td>2001</td>
          <td>2002</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
          <td>England</td>
          <td>8,500</td>
          <td>8,600</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
          <td>East Riding of Yorkshire</td>
          <td>35</td>
          <td>30</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
          <td><sup>1</sup> Includes secure units, children's homes and hostels, residential schools and other residential settings</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
          <td><sup>2</sup> All data are rounded&#x2014;national figures to the nearest 100 and local authority figures to the nearest 5</td>
          </tr></table></p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
